    "This discrepancy in the scaling behavior of light nuclei dv 1 ∕dy| y=0 at energies below 7.7 GeV and above 11.5 GeV may indicate a different production mechanism or system evolution, as the QGP is expected to form at higher energies, and interactions occur at the partonic level [91,92].Hypernuclei are nuclei containing at least one hyperon.",
